@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{pdf-tools-extras.el} extends the @samp{pdf-tools} package with commands and functions that improve everyday PDF workflows in Emacs. The built-in @samp{pdf-tools} is excellent for viewing and annotating PDFs, but certain operations---opening a PDF in an external viewer at the current page, extracting all text, adapting the display to the active theme---require additional code. This package fills those gaps.

The main areas of functionality are:

@itemize
@item
PDF conversion: extracting text from PDFs via @samp{pdftotext} (@ref{PDF conversion}).
@item
Theme integration: automatically toggling midnight mode to match the active Modus theme (@ref{Theme integration}).
@item
Text operations: counting words, copying text with DWIM behavior, and enhanced highlight annotations (@ref{Text operations}).
@item
External interaction: opening the PDF in an external viewer at the current page, toggling @samp{writeroom-mode}, deleting the file (@ref{External interaction}).
@item
Ebib integration: jumping from a PDF to the corresponding Bib@TeX{} entry (@ref{Ebib integration}).
@item
Experimental word selection via double-click (@ref{Word selection}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{pdf-tools} and optionally integrates with @samp{modus-themes}, @samp{writeroom-mode}, and @samp{ebib-extras.el}.

