@node PDF conversion
@section PDF conversion

@vindex pdf-tools-extras-pdftotext-executable
The variable @code{pdf-tools-extras-pdftotext-executable} holds the path to the @samp{pdftotext} executable (default @samp{"pdftotext"}). Customize it if the executable is installed in a non-standard location.

@findex pdf-tools-extras-convert-pdf
The function @code{pdf-tools-extras-convert-pdf} converts a PDF file to plain text. It accepts a SOURCE file path and an optional DESTINATION. When DESTINATION is non-nil, the text is written to that file; otherwise, the text is returned as a string. This is the main entry point for PDF text extraction and is used by other packages such as @samp{read-aloud-extras.el}.

@findex pdf-tools-extras--run-pdftotext
Internally, @code{pdf-tools-extras--run-pdftotext} runs the @samp{pdftotext} executable on a SOURCE file, writing to OUTPUT (a file path or @samp{"-"} for stdout). It accepts an optional EXTRA-ARGS list for additional flags such as margin settings. It signals an error if @samp{pdftotext} is not installed.

@node Theme integration
@section Theme integration

@findex pdf-tools-extras-apply-theme
Reading a bright-white PDF in a dark Emacs theme is unpleasant, and @samp{pdf-tools} provides @code{pdf-view-midnight-minor-mode} to invert colors. The function @code{pdf-tools-extras-apply-theme} inspects the currently active Modus theme and enables midnight mode if the theme has a dark background, or disables it for a light background. This function is intended to be called from a theme-change hook so that PDFs automatically adapt when you switch themes.

Internally, it calls @code{modus-themes-get-current-theme} and reads the @samp{:background-mode} property from the theme's metadata to determine whether the theme is dark or light.

@node Word selection
@section Word selection

@vindex pdf-tools-extras-sel-mode-map
@findex pdf-tools-extras-sel-mouse
The file includes an experimental minor mode @code{pdf-tools-extras-sel-mode} that binds double-click (@samp{[double-mouse-1]}) to @code{pdf-tools-extras-sel-mouse}. This command selects the word under the mouse cursor in the PDF and copies it to the kill ring using @code{pdf-info-getselection} and @code{pdf-info-gettext} with the @samp{'word} selection granularity.

As noted in the source code, this feature is experimental: double-clicking sometimes selects more text than the intended word, and upstream @samp{pdf-tools} may eventually incorporate similar functionality. The mode is enabled globally at load time.

